{
  "abstract": "Aflatoxin contamination of groundnut or peanut (Arachis hypogaea L.) is a widespread serious\r\nproblem in most groundnut-producing countries where the crop is grown under rainfed conditions. The\r\nsemi-arid tropical environment is conducive to preharvest contamination when the crop experiences\r\ndrought before harvest, whereas in the wet and humid areas, postharvest contamination is more\r\nprevalent. Breeding",
